Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): This paper proposes an end-to-end framework for mapping print defects using Convolutional Neural Networks and semantic segmentation. The use of computer vision techniques and deep learning models makes this paper highly relevant to the cs.CV sub-category.
2. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the analysis of printed images, which can be considered a form of multimedia. The use of image processing and computer graphics techniques to simulate print defects also makes this paper relevant to the cs.MM sub-category.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of deep learning models to map print defects falls under the scope of the cs.AI sub-category. The paper proposes an efficient and automated approach to this task, which is highly relevant to the field of AI.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The use of deep learning models for semantic segmentation and defect mapping makes this paper relevant to the cs.LG sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of synthetic training data, which is a common technique in machine learning.
5. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper uses computer graphics techniques to simulate print defects, which makes it relevant to the cs.GR sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of image processing techniques, which are commonly used in graphics applications.
